<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-19T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-19T08:00:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/7–1949:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Lebanon</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Pinkerton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-19T15:00:00+02:00">July
                                        19, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>369. Re <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss>, July 16.
                                Lebanese Delegation to Lausanne has been impressed with need to
                                reach agreement on outstanding issues being discussed and it has
                                received instructions from President and Prime Minister to cooperate
                                fully with <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss>. Principal delegate
                                has been given full authority in negotiations. In two conversations
                                I had with him during his stay Lebanon, he indicated complete
                                willingness to cooperate and so far as Lebanon is concerned
                                realization of urgency for finding solution on all points. Foreign
                                Office says Turk Chargé has made similar approach and has received
                                similar assurances.<note n="1" xml:id="d841fn1">The Department, on
                                    July 20, directed Beirut to “Convey to Pres and <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> US appreciation Leb
                                    cooperative attitude re <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss>
                                    negots and instru[ction]s this regard to principal Leb delegate
                                    Lausanne” (telegram 353, 501.BB Palestine/7–1949).</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Pinkerton</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>